  "result": "**Merge** preserves history as-is: combines two branches by creating a new merge commit with two parents. Non-destructive, keeps the full branching topology.\n\n**Rebase** rewrites history: replays your commits on top of another branch, producing a linear sequence with new commit hashes. Cleaner log, but the original commits are gone.\n\nRules of thumb:\n- Rebase local/private branches before sharing — clean up before others see them.\n- Merge shared branches — never rebase commits others have pulled (force-push rewrites their history).\n- `git pull --rebase` for keeping a feature branch current without merge-commit noise.",
